AUTHORING INTERFACE SETUP GUIDE

BACKEND
Step1: Create the folder named AuthInterface
# Step2: Clone the project using path
Step3: Go to the folder using "cd AuthInterface"
Step4: Setup Virtual Environment, Run the following commands in terminal
    python3 -m venv env
    source env/bin/activate
Step5: Then install the requirements using
    pip install -r requirements.txt
Step6: open the function displayUSR in the file app.py, Change the path of mentioned USR_Generator directories with that of your device path
Step7: run "python3 main.py" inorder to run the backend code
Step8: hit the api "http://127.0.0.1:9999/" to enable the creation of databases.


FRONTEND
Step9: Let the above backend running and open the new terminal and run the following commands
    "npm install"
    "cd client"
    "npm install react-router-dom"
    "npm install axios"
    "npm run start"

**FINISH**
# to create react app:
# npx create-react-app client
# client in 
# package.json : "proxy":"http://127.0.0.1:9999"

# run:
# cd client
# npm install react-router-dom
# npm install axios
# npm i react-flash-message
# npm run start

